**Description**

This endpoint initializes an automation request by setting up all necessary references and action connections in the provided `G4AutomationModel`. The result is an initialized model that is ready for invocation.

**Request Body**

The request body must contain a `G4AutomationModel`, which specifies the configuration and parameters for initializing the automation session. This includes authentication details, driver settings, and stage definitions, each containing one or more jobs to be executed.

**Fields:**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| authentication | object | Yes | Specifies authentication details, including username for API access. |
| driverParameters | object | Yes | Configurations related to the browser driver and capabilities for the automation session. |
| stages | array | Yes | List of stages, each containing at least one job. |
| jobs | array | Yes | Jobs to be executed within each stage, with rules and configurations for automation. |

